          <p style="line-height: 35px; font-size: 20px;">Water your plant regularly, but avoid overwatering. Make sure the soil is moist but not waterlogged.<br>
            Ensure that your plant is receiving the right amount of sunlight. Some plants need direct sunlight, while others prefer indirect light.<br>
            Check your plant for pests and diseases regularly. If you notice any issues, take action immediately to prevent the problem from spreading.<br>
            Prune your plant regularly to keep it healthy and promote new growth. Remove any dead or damaged leaves or stems.<br>
            Fertilize your plant every few months to provide it with the nutrients it needs to thrive.<br>
            Choose the right type of potting soil for your plant, and repot it when necessary.<br>
            Keep your plant away from drafts, as this can cause stress and damage.<br>
            Monitor the humidity levels in your home, and consider using a humidifier if your plant requires high humidity.<br>
            Rotate your plant periodically to ensure even growth and exposure to light.
            </p>
